        int[] dy = {0, 1, 0, -1};

        for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
            int nx = x + dx[i];
            int ny = y + dy[i];

            // Check if the move is within the board
            if (nx >= 0 && nx < size && ny >= 0 && ny < size) {
                Place destination = new Place(nx, ny);
                Move move = new Move(source, destination);
                moves.add(move);
            }
        }

        return moves.toArray(new Move[0]);
    }
}
```

This code creates a list of all possible moves for the Archer piece. It checks each of the four possible directions (up, down, left, right) from the current position. If the move is within the board, it is added to the list of available moves. The list is then converted to an array and returned.

